Author: the_second_morgan
Content:
Right, this will be the start of me reviewing movies as I am a big cinephile on these things.

Morgan Movie Moviews #1:
`Le Samourai.` - Jean-Pierre Melville (1967) **(8/10)**

```"A slow, but a very cool movie nonetheless. From the title itself, everyone will misunderstood this for a Japanese movie made by a Frenchie but no. Jean Melville actually delves into the Bushido or the code of samurai and implements it on this character, portrayed by Alain Delon, otherise known as Jef Costello.

Jef Costello is an assassin working with only few uses of the tongue. He has a bird in his room, a pair of keys that he uses to hijack cars and a signature beige trenchcoat and gray hat whenever he goes around. He's silent, he's composed, and he embodies what a modern 'samurai' would look like. The movie has its own style in itself too, and oftentimes, it can be very intriguing.

Overall, this has to be one of those night-time movies to watch within the category of "French New Wave".```

Author: the_second_morgan
Content:
NB:
It is also an adaptation of a novel by Joan McLeod called "The Ronin."

Author: the_second_morgan
Content:
Morgan Movie Moviews #2:
`Fallen Angels` - Wong Kar-Wai (1995) **(9/10)**

```"A movie of two stories, one a hitman who struggles to leave the criminal underworld, the other a mute ex-convict who met with a girl after getting dumped off by her boyfriend.

This movie will put you on a train of emotions, combined with the cinematic aesthetics of Wong Kar-Wai, and its choice of colors, this is honestly a pretty unique watch. You'll laugh, you'll cry, hell you'll be blasted with nostalgia and seldom-felt sonder. Some scenes will stick on the back of your head and even after multiple watches of this movie, it had stained you the moment you put this film down for a watch for the first time.

The movie that, for me, gets me the most feels from."```

Author: the_second_morgan
Content:
Morgan Movie Moviews #3:
`Assault on Precinct 13` - John Carpenter (1976) **(8.5/10)**

```"Assault on Precinct 13, one of the underrated movies released by the legend, John Carpenter. It tells the story of one Lieutenant Ethan Bishop who is sent to take charge on a decommissioned precinct before it closes. However, a group of gangsters who signed themselves a blood pact plans to assault the precinct as an act of revenge. These events later on would determine if the precinct stays standing on its foundations or ravaged.

This film has a wild west taste to it, and Carpenter still delivers on the thriller aspect of the movie. Coupled with some not-over-the-top but carefully thought out action where both characters struggle to defend the precinct from ever getting breached by these gangsters. It's truly spectacular, it was an awesome watch but it gets underwhelming in some parts of the movie.

Overall, a very interesting watch from Carpenter himself."```

Author: the_second_morgan
Content:
Morgan Movie Moviews #4:
`√Ä bout de souffle / Breathless` - Jean-Luc Godard (1960) **(9/10)**

```"Another cool cinematic masterpiece of the classic French New Wave, this time coming from the likes of Jean-Luc Godard. And like Godard's way of telling stories, the characters are oddly playful, giving it a sense of comedy in everything. Nevertheless, this is a romantic story of a criminal on the run who later found a woman as the police continued to tail him down.

Everything about this movie just oozes in the aesthetics you would normally find in any romantic movie, but if it's Godard we're talking about. There's more than just being romantic or crime-driven in its themes. The tension is there, and the plot twist at the end and that careful, confused send-off gave it all away for me. This movie is why I have loved Godard ever since I first watched it when I was 15 years old, and rewatching it feels like nostalgia all over again.

Definitely a must-see for those who wants to plunge in to the French New Wave."```

Author: kin.1212
Content: I just finished severance season one and I'm obsessed

Author: kin.1212
Content:
Since I don't have anyone to talk to about it, I made a review:

Severance is an ongoing thriller, sci-fi, and mystery series by Apple TV that‚Äôs directed by the well-known, Emmy-winning director Ben Stiller. In season 1, Severance had 9 episodes.

The story follows a world where a company with the name Lumon has this unique procedure that has to make their workers brains to be split in half, not allowing their memory in the work place to be preserved outside of it, and the same goes for the outside memorises.

It‚Äôs like having two different lives and living as two different people but in the same body.
Our main character, Mark S. (portrayed by Adam Scott), leads the Macrodata Refinement department. With his subordinates, Irving B. (portrayed by John Turturro), Dylan G. (portrayed by Zach Cherry), and their newest addition, Helly R. (portrayed by Britt Lower), who replaced their past Chief, Petey K. (portrayed by Yul Vazquez).  We followed along those mundane office works to the most unpredictable ones together with the four Macrodata Refinement workers.

Season 1, so far, in my opinion, has incredible storytelling in both visual and auditory forms. They want us to feel isolated and at ease with the most absurd scenario or environment. Especially with its minimalist and precise work environment. I‚Äôm obsessed with the colours and cinematography in it. And as someone who‚Äôs constantly awkward, I find myself seeing that the characters here are way, way more awkward, so it made me feel at ease lol.

I can assure you that a lot of why's, what's, and how's are gonna come out of your mouth with each episode being watched.

If you like conspiracy, mystery amongs industry, and a little bit of cult in it. Severance might be a great series to get you invested. 

I cannot talk about Severance without spoilering it, but there will be queer characters and people dying. 

With that, I‚Äôll give Severance Season 1 a ‚Öò star.

(possible bukit duri spoilers) || first off what do you think about the way the movie uses recent historical event? i personally really like the fact that they bring up events that happened in 98, but apparently some people disagree. they think the movie only uses this historical event and inter-ethnic conflict as mere background for the action thriller that happened.

for me though i think there is a lack of any kind of media that talks about the racially-motivated violence that happened in '98. especially as gen z i think people tend to shove off inter-ethnic conflicts between "pribumi" and "chindo" as something of the past. though in reality, the conflict is quite far from over. there are still heat and sparks going on. so i'm *really* glad that there is even one big movie bringing up this subject.||

Author: ekast237707
Content:
1. Autumn dan Semesta yang Lain ‚Äì Rintik Sedu
Buat kamu yang suka kalimat-kalimat puitis penuh rasa, buku ini bakal cocok banget. Rintik Sedu emang jagonya bikin tulisan yang relate sama realita cinta dan hidup sehari-hari.

2. Mariposa ‚Äì Luluk HF
Kisah cinta remaja yang manis tapi nggak lebay. Cerita Acha dan Iqbal ini sempat viral dan bahkan difilmkan, lho!

3. Laut Bercerita ‚Äì Leila S. Chudori
Kalau kamu suka cerita sejarah yang dibungkus drama keluarga dan persahabatan, ini pilihan wajib. Menggugah hati dan bikin kamu mikir ulang tentang keadilan.

4. Negeri 5 Menara ‚Äì Ahmad Fuadi
Buku ini bukan cuma inspiratif, tapi juga nyuguhin petualangan yang bikin kamu pengen terus belajar dan keliling dunia. Man Jadda Wajada, kan?

5. Selamat Tinggal ‚Äì Tere Liye
Tere Liye emang selalu berhasil nyentuh sisi emosional pembaca. Buku ini ngajak kamu merenung tentang masa lalu dan keberanian untuk move on.

6. Hujan ‚Äì Tere Liye
Masih dari penulis yang sama, Hujan punya sentuhan fiksi ilmiah, cinta, dan dilema hidup. Perpaduan yang unik dan bikin nagih.

7. Garis Waktu ‚Äì Fiersa Besari
Isi buku ini penuh kutipan galau yang cocok dibaca waktu kamu lagi overthinking. Bisa dibilang ini buku puisi cinta buat generasi sekarang.

8. Bumi (Seri Dunia Paralel) ‚Äì Tere Liye
Kalau kamu penggemar fiksi fantasi ala Indonesia, seri Bumi ini bisa banget jadi pelarian dari dunia nyata. Petualangannya seru abis!

9. Kata ‚Äì Rintik Sedu
Kisah cinta yang pahit-manis tapi dibawakan dengan gaya bahasa yang adem. Cocok buat nemenin malam sendumu.

10. Dilan: Dia adalah Dilanku Tahun 1990 ‚Äì Pidi Baiq
Siapa sih yang nggak kenal Dilan? Romansa anak SMA yang kocak, nyeleneh, tapi juga bikin deg-degan.

11. Janji ‚Äì Tere Liye
Salah satu karya Tere Liye yang penuh nilai moral dan kebijaksanaan. Ceritanya ringan tapi maknanya dalam banget.

12. Critical Eleven ‚Äì Ika Natassa
Buat kamu yang suka drama dewasa dengan dialog cerdas dan konflik emosional, ini salah satu yang terbaik.

13. Sabtu Bersama Bapak ‚Äì Adhitya Mulya
Buku ini punya sentuhan keluarga yang hangat dan lucu, tapi juga penuh pesan bijak. Nggak heran jadi best seller!

14. Tentang Kamu ‚Äì Tere Liye
Novel ini gabungin unsur misteri, drama, dan kehidupan dengan cara yang bikin kamu terus pengen lanjut baca sampai akhir.

15. Filosofi Teras ‚Äì Henry Manampiring
Nggak melulu fiksi, buku nonfiksi ini juga masuk jajaran best seller. Isinya ngajarin kamu buat lebih tenang dan waras dalam hidup, pakai prinsip stoikisme.

Author: chewiezzz
Content:
I like how the movie confronts generational trauma head-on in the movie, especially in the beginning to set up the mood for the rest of the movie. The inter-ethnic conflict runs deeper than just racial imo, there's also religious conflict mentioned in the movie, albeit just a little. But I think the core moral message is about how father figure is important, and Joko Anwar uses the tragedy of 98 to provide a more dramatic background to communicate that message, so people's opinion are not entirely wrong there.

As for the media, I think it's because racial and religious conflict is still considered a "taboo" to be discussed in depth here, but I am sure glad that Joko Anwar made a movie about it, so I expect there will be more discussions in podcast or other independent media in social media about these issues soon.

Speaking from experience, as I'm a chindo male also, some chindo girl (not all ofc) tends to see non-chindo girl as "inferior" and that she has to marry another chindo male to keep the blood "pure" so to speak. So, the chindo chick may feel irritated that she lose to a non-chindo girl in the "romantic competition".

Author: ekast237707
Content:
Isi

7 Buku Fiksi Indonesia yang Wajib Kamu Koleksi
7 May 2025

Author: ekast237707
Content:
*
Buku Fiksi Indonesia ‚Äì Buat kamu pecinta buku, khususnya fiksi Indonesia, pasti udah nggak asing lagi dengan banyak karya keren dari penulis-penulis lokal. Mulai dari yang bikin baper, ngakak, sampe yang penuh makna dan pesan hidup, semuanya lengkap.

Author: ekast237707
Content:
*
1. Laskar Pelangi ‚Äì Andrea Hirata
Buku ini udah jadi legenda di dunia literasi Indonesia. Laskar Pelangi nyeritain tentang perjuangan anak-anak dari desa Gantong yang penuh semangat buat sekolah meski dalam keterbatasan. Kisahnya inspiratif banget dan penuh nilai kehidupan yang bikin kamu makin bersyukur.

2. Perahu Kertas ‚Äì Dee Lestari
Kalau kamu suka kisah cinta yang nggak biasa, Perahu Kertas wajib banget masuk wishlist. Buku ini nyuguhin cerita tentang dua orang dengan mimpi besar yang terus berusaha nemuin jalan mereka masing-masing, sambil bertanya-tanya, ‚Äúkita ini ditakdirin bareng nggak sih?‚Äù

3. Supernova ‚Äì Dee Lestari
Seri Supernova adalah paket lengkap buat kamu yang suka filosofi, sains, dan cinta digabung jadi satu. Tulisannya unik, pemikirannya dalem, dan bikin kamu merenung berkali-kali. Nggak heran kalau buku ini punya fans setia sejak awal diterbitin.

4. Amba ‚Äì Laksmi Pamuntjak
Buku ini nyuguhin kisah cinta yang berlatar sejarah kelam Indonesia, yaitu tragedi 1965. Amba bukan cuma cerita cinta, tapi juga perjuangan, kehilangan, dan pencarian jati diri. Nggak heran kalau buku ini banyak direkomendasikan di komunitas sastra.

5. O ‚Äì Eka Kurniawan
Penulis yang satu ini dikenal banget sama gaya bahasanya yang khas dan cerita-cerita yang absurd tapi penuh makna. O adalah novel yang menggambarkan dunia hewan sebagai metafora kehidupan manusia. Seru, beda, dan penuh sindiran sosial yang cerdas.

6. Cerita Cinta Enrico ‚Äì Ayu Utami
Ayu Utami emang terkenal berani dalam menyuarakan isu-isu sensitif. Di Cerita Cinta Enrico, kamu bakal diajak buat ngelihat bagaimana kehidupan seorang pria yang tumbuh di tengah perubahan sosial dan budaya yang cukup dramatis. Buku ini punya nuansa yang dalam dan nggak biasa.

7. Pulang ‚Äì Leila S. Chudori
Kalau kamu suka cerita yang berbau sejarah, politik, dan keluarga, Pulang bisa jadi pilihan pas. Buku ini nyeritain tentang eksil politik Indonesia yang harus hidup di luar negeri akibat situasi politik di masa Orde Baru. Ceritanya kuat, emosional, dan penuh wawasan sejarah.

Buku-buku fiksi Indonesia itu nggak kalah keren sama karya luar. Ceritanya dekat sama kehidupan kita, bahasanya nyentuh, dan banyak pesan yang bisa kamu ambil. Jadi, yuk mulai koleksi 7 buku di atas, siapa tahu bisa jadi sumber inspirasi atau bahkan penyemangat di hari-harimu!

Content: The film, which is Palestine‚Äôs entry to the Oscars, has a lot of story to tell, but still manages to singularly draw its many characters and to give specificity to its different locations. It demands the audience‚Äôs undivided attention and earns it by the end of its running time.

Author: ekast237707
Content: ‚ÄúPalestine 36‚Äù resonates because it binds the personal to the political, showing how resistance emerges in both quiet and explosive forms. Jacir‚Äôs film reminds that history is not abstract, but lived through families and small moments of solidarity and conflict. By uniting epic scope with intimate detail, it delivers a portrait of a people fractured yet unbroken. When it hits its final note, a catharsis is felt by the audience as history and today‚Äôs reality intertwine.

Author: ramabilek_
Content:
Menceritakan tentang keresahan seorang penulis wanita(Bell Hooks) yang bercerita tentang cinta & hubungan. Ia merasa bahwa penulis laki laki lebih dihargai dibanding penulis perempuan. Dikarenakan, laki laki berpikir secara logis dan mendalam sedangkan wanita berpikir dengan perasaan/feeling. Bell Hooks, Si penulis buku ini ingin membuktikan bahwa penulis perempuan juga bisa menghasilkan hasil karya yang lebih bagus dibandingkan karya tulis laki laki. 

Isi dari buku ini terbagi menjadi 13, yaitu:
‚Ä¢ Kejelasan
‚Ä¢ Keadilan 
‚Ä¢ Kejujuran 
‚Ä¢ Komitmen
‚Ä¢ Spiritualitas 
‚Ä¢ Nilai-nilai
‚Ä¢ Keserakahan
‚Ä¢ Komunitas 
‚Ä¢ Keterhubungan 
‚Ä¢ Romansa
‚Ä¢ Kehilangan
‚Ä¢ Pemulihan
‚Ä¢ Takdir

Buku yang lumayan bagus lah buat seseorang yang ingin mengenal lebih dalam tentang percintaan dan hubungan antara laki laki & perempuan.

Author: ekast237707
Content:
. 
***Meningkatkan Empati
Selain itu, fiksi meningkatkan kapasitas empati kita. Saat kita membaca tentang perjuangan seorang tokoh yang mengalami diskriminasi, kemiskinan, atau kehilangan, hati kita turut merasakan kepedihan mereka. Penelitian menunjukkan bahwa orang yang rajin membaca fiksi sastra memiliki kemampuan lebih baik dalam mendeteksi emosi orang lain di kehidupan nyata. Akibatnya, mereka menjadi teman, pasangan, atau pemimpin yang lebih pengertian***
